    • Method Detail

      • addSerDeProperties

        public void addSerDeProperties(Path path,
                               HiveRegistrationUnit hiveUnit)
                        throws IOException
        Add an Avro Schema to the given HiveRegistrationUnit.

        If USE_SCHEMA_FILE is true, the schema will be added via SCHEMA_URL pointing to the schema file named SCHEMA_FILE_NAME.

        If USE_SCHEMA_FILE is false, the schema will be obtained by getDirectorySchema(Path). If the length of the schema is less than SCHEMA_LITERAL_LENGTH_LIMIT, it will be added via SCHEMA_LITERAL. Otherwise, the schema will be written to SCHEMA_FILE_NAME and added via SCHEMA_URL.

        Specified by:
        addSerDeProperties in class HiveSerDeManager
        Parameters:
        path - The Path from where the schema should be obtained.
        hiveUnit - The HiveRegistrationUnit where the serde properties should be added to.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • addSerDeProperties

        public void addSerDeProperties(HiveRegistrationUnit source,
                               HiveRegistrationUnit target)
                        throws IOException
        Description copied from class: HiveSerDeManager
        Add the appropriate SerDe properties (including schema properties) to the target HiveRegistrationUnit using the SerDe properties from the source HiveRegistrationUnit.

        A benefit of doing this is to avoid obtaining the schema multiple times when creating a table and a partition with the same schema, or creating several tables and partitions with the same schema. After the first table/partition is created, one can use the same SerDe properties to create the other tables/partitions.

        Specified by:
        addSerDeProperties in class HiveSerDeManager
        Throws:
        IOException

      • addSchemaFromAvroFile

        protected void addSchemaFromAvroFile(Schema schema,
                                     Path schemaFile,
                                     HiveRegistrationUnit hiveUnit)
                              throws IOException
        Add a Schema obtained from an Avro data file to the given HiveRegistrationUnit.

        If the length of the schema is less than SCHEMA_LITERAL_LENGTH_LIMIT, it will be added via SCHEMA_LITERAL. Otherwise, the schema will be written to SCHEMA_FILE_NAME and added via SCHEMA_URL.

        Throws:
        IOException
